Re: What does 〜て　おきます mean?
by squarezebra » Sat 09.11.2010 8:50 am whenever you see つもり its about intention. サッカをするつもりです　(I intend to play football)映画を見たつもりだったが残念宿題がありました。 (I had intended to watch the movie but unfortunately I had homework to do.)　Might I recommend you purchase a copy of A Dictionary of Basic Japanese Grammar? Very thorough, and tons of example sentences for each grammar entry.
Spend less time thinking, and more time doing. squarezebra
